\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 1) Srila Prabhupada\rquote s spiritual master Srila Bhaktisiddhanta Saraswati Thakur had ordered him to preach the message of Bhagavad Gita all over the world, specially in the western countries. Srila Prabhupada took this desire of his spiritual master to his heart and made this as the mission of his life.
\par    In order to execute the order of his spiritual master Srila Prabhupada decided to go to America. With great difficulty he managed to get a free ticket on a Scindia cargo ship going to Boston.
\par    Enroute to Boston Srila Prabhupada encountered great difficulty. He noted in his diary:
\par \ldblquote Rain, seasickness, dizziness, headache, no appetite, vomiting. \rdblquote The symptoms persisted, but it was more than seasickness. In two days he suffered two heart attacks. He tolerated the difficulties, knowing them to be temporary, while meditating on the purpose of his mission.
\par    Externally Srila Prabhupada was experiencing great inconveniences; he had been aboard ship for a month and had suffered heart attacks and repeated seasickness. Moreover, even if he were to recover from these difficulties, his arrival in America would undoubtedly bring many more difficulties. He was seventy years old, had no prior knowledge of America, no base of support and only Rs. 40/- in his pocket. But remembering the desire of his spiritual master and praying to Lord Krishna, Srila Prabhupada remained confident and determined.
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 
\par Mention in the box below, which Quality (one or more) of Srila Prabhupada is highlighted in the above anecdote ?
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22  }{\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par 2) After reaching New York, Srila Prabhupada had been living in Manhattan. He was doing His translation work and preaching to the people there.
\par     But then some young people who used to come to see Srila Prabhupada from downtown area of New York called Bowery advised Him to shift downtown as there were many young people interested in knowing about spiritual life.
\par     The Bowery was no place for a gentleman. It was the most corrupt place in the world. It is still known all over the world as skid row, a place of ruined and homeless alcoholics. At night, those without lodging slept on the sidewalks, doorsteps and street corners. Theft\rquote s were common place; a man\rquote s pockets might be searched ten or twenty times while he slept. The rates of hospitalization and death in the Bowery were five times higher than the national average, and many of the homeless bore the marks of recent injuries or violence.
\par      Inspite of all these dangers Srila Prabhupada decided to move to Bowery for preaching the message of Bhagavad Gita. He was totally fearless ! Srila Prabhupada later recalled \ldblquote  My friend was shocked to hear that I was moving to the Bowery but although I passed through many dangers, I never thought that, \lquote This is danger!\rquote .\rdblquote 
\par   
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 Mention in the box below, which Quality (one or more) of Srila Prabhupada is highlighted in the above anecdote ?
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22 \page 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 3) It was 1966, Radha-Krishna Temple, New York. Srila Prabhupada was giving a lecture on Bhagavad Gita in a downtown area called Bowery. The young audience of 100 or so were silently and respectfully listening to his lecture. Suddenly a Bowery homeless, a drunkard, entered, whistling and drunkenly shouting. The audience remained seated not knowing what to make of it.
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 
\par Drunk:}{\f1\fs22  \ldblquote How are Ya?\rdblquote 
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 Prabhupada}{\f1\fs22 : \ldblquote Don\rquote t disturb. Sit Down. We are talking seriously.\rdblquote 
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 Drunk}{\f1\fs22 : \ldblquote Is it a Church? All right. I\rquote ll be right back.\rdblquote 
\par 
\par     The man was white-haired, with a short grizzly beard and wore dirty, smelly clothes. His odor reeked through the temple. Then he suddenly stumbled out of the door and was gone. Prabhupada chuckled softly and returned immediately to his lecture.
\par 
\par Suddenly the drunk returned, announcing his entrance.  \ldblquote How are Ya?\rdblquote  
\par 
\par He was carrying something! He maneuvered his way through the audience, straight to the back of the temple towards the toilets. He opened the toilet door, put two boxes of soaps inside and changed the bathroom tissue above the sink.
\par 
\par Srila Prabhupada looked at him and asked, 
\par \ldblquote  What is this ?\rdblquote . The drunk was silent now; he had done his work! Prabhupada began to laugh thanking his visitor, who moved towards the door: \ldblquote Thank You. Thank You very much.\rdblquote  The bum went out.
\par  
\par \ldblquote Just see,\rdblquote  Prabhupada addressed his audience. \ldblquote It is a natural tendency to give some service. Just see he is not in order, but he thought that, \lquote Here is something(to do). Let me give some service. Just see how automatically it comes. This is natural.\rdblquote 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 Srila Prabhupada only appreciated his service attitude, ignoring the bad qualities of that man.
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Mention in the box below, which Quality (one or more) of Srila Prabhupada is highlighted in the above anecdote ?
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i\f1\fs22  
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\b\f1\fs22 
\par \page }{\f1\fs22 4) Srila Prabhupada was giving a University lecture in Paris to a group of radical students. He was sitting on a raised seat(called }{\i\f1\fs22 Vyasasana}{\f1\fs22 ). Many of his disciples were also present and were giving Him respect as a bona-fide guru in a way which a Westerner is not familiar with.
\par     He was talking about the }{\i\f1\fs22 varnasrama dharma}{\f1\fs22  where the whole society is divided into four classes (}{\i\f1\fs22 sudra}{\f1\fs22 , }{\i\f1\fs22 vaisya, ksatriya & brahmana}{\f1\fs22 ) according to their aptitude and not by birth. Srila Prabhupada was telling that }{\i\f1\fs22 Brahmanas }{\f1\fs22 should be first class men  who intelligently lead the society. }{\i\f1\fs22 Ksatriyas}{\f1\fs22  are second class men who administer the government, }{\i\f1\fs22 Vaisyas}{\f1\fs22  are third class who do business and }{\i\f1\fs22 sudras}{\f1\fs22  are fourth class men who are dependent on others and work for them. He said that he wants to create some first class men in the world who can guide the rest of the society.
\par    One of the students from the crowd came forward and challenged \ldblquote  Oh! Then you must be a first class man, Swami?\rdblquote 
\par     When the question was translated into English to Srila Prabhupada, he became silent. There was nervous tittering among the students. One could feel the tension hung in the air. The silence continued for a while. Everyone was nervously waiting for the reply. One could see Srila Prabhupada had become more meditative. 
\par     Finally he replied in a grave tone, \ldblquote No! I am not 1st class. I am the servant of all the four classes. Actually, I am 5th class.\rdblquote 
\par     Even before the answer was translated back to the audience in French, just by his tone everyone had become respectful. He had shown his natural humility as a servant of God serving everyone to help make them a God-Conscious person.
\par 
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 Mention in the box below, which Quality (one or more) of Srila Prabhupada is highlighted in the above anecdote ?
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \pvpara\phpg\posx1470\posy94\absh289\absw9877\dxfrtext180\dfrmtxtx180\dfrmtxty0\adjustright {
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 5) Once Srila Prabhupada was giving a lecture on Bhagavad Gita. There were more than 1000 people listening very attentively to his class. Everyone was in a very serious and respectful mood. 
\par Suddenly one young boy of around 20 years of age got up from the crowd and started shouting at Srila Prabhupada. He was pointing his finger at Srila Prabhupada and yelling at Him. There seemed to be no reason for him to act in that way. 
\par     The whole crowd became very silent not knowing what to do. Srila Prabhupada\rquote s disciples became angry at that boy for insulting their spiritual master and wanted to take action against him but Srila Prabhupada gestured not to pay attention to him.
\par     Srila Prabhupada was completely undisturbed and continued with his lecture not showing any sign of anger at the boy\rquote s misbehaviour. After some time the boy left the place on his own. 
\par     After the class his disciples asked Srila Prabhupada \ldblquote  That boy was shouting at you for no reason still you did not say anything ? Why didn\rquote t you let us do something ?\rdblquote 
\par     Srila Prabhupada replied very gravely, \ldblquote  No, I must have done something wrong to him in my previous life that is why he was shouting at me. Otherwise for no reason he will not shout at me.\rdblquote 
\par 
\par }{\i\f1\fs22 Mention in the box below, which Quality (one or more) of Srila Prabhupada is highlighted in the above anecdote ?
